# Spin-Boson Examples

As a first example, let us simulate the non-equilibrium dynamics corresponding to the famous Spin-Boson model, where all the parameters are specified in atomic units.

```toml
[system]
Hamiltonian = "Hamiltonian"

[baths]
beta = 5.0
[[baths.bath]]
type = "ohmic"
xi = 0.1
omegac = 7.5
svec = [1.0, -1.0]
```

Notice that the `[units]` section is completely skipped over because the default values specify atomic units. While the spin-boson problem can be used with any general Hamiltonian, let us try to see the results with an asymmetric Hamiltonian, ``H = \begin{pmatrix}1.0 & -1.0\\ -1.0 & -1.0\end{pmatrix}``
